## Bibliography (pp. 441-454)

### Key Academic Works Referenced

**Information Theory & Communication**
- **Claude Shannon** - "A Mathematical Theory of Communication" (Bell System Technical Journal, 1948) and full book (University of Illinois Press, 1949)
- Shannon's collected papers edited by **Neil J. A. Sloane** and **Aaron D. Wyner** (IEEE Press, 1993)
- **John R. Pierce** - *An Introduction to Information Theory: Symbols, Signals and Noise* (Dover, 1980)
- **Peter Elias** - "Two Famous Papers" (IRE Transactions on Information Theory, 1958)
- **J. L. Kelly, Jr.** - "A New Interpretation of Information Rate" (Bell System Technical Journal, 1956)

**Portfolio Theory & Investment Mathematics**
- **Harry M. Markowitz** - "Portfolio Selection" (Journal of Finance, 1952) and book versions (Wiley 1959, Yale 1970)
- **Paul A. Samuelson** - extensive work on portfolio theory including "General Proof That Diversification Pays" (1967), "Lifetime Portfolio Selection by Dynamic Stochastic Programming" (1969)
- **William F. Sharpe** - "Capital Asset Prices: A Theory of Market Equilibrium Under Conditions of Risk" (Journal of Finance, 1964)
- **Eugene Fama** - "Efficient Capital Markets" papers (Journal of Finance, 1970, 1991)
- **Robert C. Merton** - "Continuous-Time Finance" (Basil Blackwell, 1990) and option pricing work

### Gambling Theory & Kelly Criterion

**Core Kelly System Papers**
- **Leo Breiman** - "Optimal Gambling Systems for Favorable Games" (Fourth Berkeley Symposium, 1961) and "Investment Policies for Expanding Businesses Optimal in a Long-Run Sense" (Naval Research Logistics Quarterly, 1960)
- **Edward O. Thorp** - "A Favorable Strategy for Twenty-one" (Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, 1961)
- **Thorp & Kassouf** - *Beat the Market: A Scientific Stock Market System* (Random House, 1967)
- **Thorp alone** - *Beat the Dealer: A Winning Strategy for the Game of Twenty-one* (Random House, 1962, revised 1966)
- **Thorp** - "Optimal Gambling Systems for Favorable Games" (Review of the International Statistical Institute, 1969)
- **Thorp** - "Portfolio Choice and the Kelly Criterion" (Proceedings of the 1971 Business and Economics Section of the American Statistical Association)

**Critiques & Debates**
- **Paul A. Samuelson** - "Why We Should Not Make Mean Log of Wealth Big Though Years to Act Are Long" (Journal of Banking and Finance, 1979)
- **Paul A. Samuelson** - "The 'Fallacy' of Maximizing the Geometric Mean in Long Sequences of Investing or Gambling" (Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, 1971)
- **Henry A. Latané** - "Criteria for Choice Among Risky Ventures" (Journal of Political Economy, 1959) and "The Geometric-Mean Principle Revisited: A Reply" (Journal of Banking and Finance, 1978)
- **Nils H. Hakansson** - "Capital Growth and the Mean-Variance Approach to Portfolio Selection" (Journal of Financial and Quantitative Analysis, 1971)
- **William T. Ziemba** and various coauthors - multiple papers on growth-optimal portfolios and Kelly criterion applications

### Blackjack & Casino Mathematics

- **Richard A. Epstein** - *Theory of Gambling and Statistical Logic* (Academic Press, 1995 revised edition)
- **Arnold Snyder** - *The Great Blackjack Hoax* (available at bjfonline.com)
- **Peter Ruchman** - "I'm Counting On You—How BJ Counting Really Started, Part III" (CasinoGaming.com, 2000)
- **Lawrence Revere** - various blackjack systems
- Casino industry coverage in *Las Vegas Style*, *Las Vegas Review-Journal*, *Orange County Register*

### Market Efficiency & Behavioral Finance

- **Burton Malkiel** - *A Random Walk Down Wall Street* (multiple editions, Norton)
- **Paul Cootner** - *The Random Character of Stock Market Prices* (MIT Press, 1964)
- **Robert Shiller** - *Irrational Exuberance* (Princeton, 2000)
- **Robert A. Haugen** - *The New Finance: The Case Against Efficient Markets* (Prentice Hall, 1999)
- **Andrei Shleifer** - work on market inefficiencies
- **D. Hirshleifer & T. Shumway** - "Good Day Sunshine: Stock Returns and the Weather" (SSRN Working Paper)

### Hedge Funds & Modern Finance

- **Mario J. Gabelli** - "The History of Hedge Funds" (online resource)
- **Roger Lowenstein** - *When Genius Failed: The Rise and Fall of Long-Term Capital Management* (Random House, 2000)
- **Sebastian Mallaby** - hedge fund coverage (*Fortune*, 2003)
- **Carol J. Loomis** - "The Jones Nobody Keeps Up With" (Fortune, 1966) and "Doing the Hedge Fund Hustle" (Fortune, 2003)
- Multiple *Wall Street Journal*, *New York Times*, and *Financial Times* articles on hedge fund performance and crashes

### Blackjack Team & Card Counting History

- **Ben Mezrich** - *Bringing Down the House* (implied reference, MIT blackjack team)
- Multiple articles from gambling industry publications on card counting systems
- Jerry Hicks - "Blackjack's No. 1 Guru" (*Los Angeles Times*, 1982)
- Coverage of casino countermeasures in various gambling magazines

### Option Pricing & Derivatives

- **Fischer Black & Myron Scholes** - foundational options pricing work
- **Robert C. Merton** - "Option Pricing When Underlying Returns Are Discontinuous" (Journal of Finance, 1976)
- **Sheen T. Kassouf** - "A Theory and an Econometric Model for Common Stock Purchase Warrants" (doctoral thesis, Columbia, 1965)
- **Merton Miller** - "The Social Costs of Some Recent Derivatives Disasters" (Pacific-Basin Finance Journal, 1996)

