### Acknowledgments Note

The acknowledgments section credits **Ed Thorp** as "especially gracious and helpful, contributing time, advice, photocopies, and speedy replies to e-mails" and noting he "read an early version of the manuscript and helped to improve its accuracy."

**Claude Shannon collection** at Library of Congress described as "invaluable resource, the more so since Shannon never chose to publish anything on investing."

**Philip I. Hershberg** credited with "asking Shannon many of the questions I would have wanted to ask him."

Extensive list of academics, finance professionals, and researchers acknowledged including **Harry M. Markowitz**, **Paul A. Samuelson**, **Robert C. Merton**, **William T. Ziemba**, **Thomas M. Cover**, and many others who contributed to the author's research.

